Lesson 7 -FOUNDRY FUND ME-:

When importing “../“ moves a directory upwards(out).

What can we do to work with addresses outside our system?
1. Unit - testing a specific part of our code
2. Integration - testing how our code works with other parts of our code
3. Forked - testing our code on a simulated real environment
4. Staging - testing our code In a real environment that is not prod.


‘’’
vm.startBroadcast;
//code
vm.stopBroadcast;
‘’’
The “vm” functionality is approachable after importing the “Script”.
Everything before “vm.startBroadcast;” is not a real TX and everything after it is a real TX.

