Lesson 9 -SMART CONTRACT LOTTERY-:

Layout of Contracts:
* Version
* Imports
* Errors
* Interfaces, libraries, contracts
* Type declarations
* State variables 
* Events
* Modifiers
* Functions

Layout of Functions:
* Constructor
* Receive function (if exists)
* Fallback function (if exists)
* External
* Public
* Internal
* Private
* View and pure functions

Events:
* Allow you to “print” tuff to the log
* Tied to the smart contract 
* Indexed parameters or non-indexed  parameters 
* They can have up to 3 indexed params
* Indexed params are also called topics. Topics are searchable in contrast to the non-indexed params. 

